SectorList.Message:
Room Prep: 

1)Thig Tourniquet
2)lpsilateral hip bump
3)Bump under ankle
4)Sterile prep and drape

Make longigudinal incision along the posterior margin of the fibula
Center incision over the fracture site

Anticipate the position of the superficial peroneal nerve crossing from the lateral to anterior compatments. 
Perform a superficial disserction through the skin subdermal layer.
Incise through the peroneal tendon sheath longitudinally and elevate peroneal muscle proximally with periosteal elevator.
Expose and open fracture site with free elevator.
